Orkla’s Wiggen Gets 45% Pay Increase After Taking Over as CEO

-- B y   M e e r a   B h a t i a
-- 
2011-03-24T07:50:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-24/orkla-s-wiggen-gets-45-pay-increase-after-taking-over-as-ceo.html
Bjoern Wiggen, who was named chief
executive officer of  Orkla ASA (ORK)  in September, received a 45
percent increase in salary and bonus last year.  Wiggen was paid 4.2 million kroner ($750,000) in ordinary
salary and a bonus of 2.24 million kroner, up from a total of
4.44 million kroner in  2009 .  Wiggen was head of Orkla’s aluminum-profiles unit Sapa
before he succeeded Dag Opedal, who was paid almost 5 million
kroner in base salary and 1.92 million kroner in bonus in 2010,
according to the company’s annual report published today.  Wiggen owns 178,869 shares in the Norwegian company whose
holdings range from frozen pizzas to aluminum assets.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Meera Bhatia in Oslo at 
 mbhatia2@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
